Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,GIRL: I'm gonna tickle you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.83,0:00:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(MUSIC PLAYING)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.97,0:00:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.94,0:00:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a refill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.98,0:00:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've already had three.\NSo what? They're free.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.45,0:00:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a birthday.\NGet it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.52,0:00:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder he doesn't\Nget any tips.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.75,0:00:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.19,0:00:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's ready to sing\Nthe Ralphie's Rumpus\Nbirthday rump shake?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SINGING)\NLet's sing, let's ride,\Nlet's bling, let's slide
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.06,0:00:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for Ralphie
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.63,0:00:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll dance, eat cake\Nand do the rump shake
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.30,0:00:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for Ralphie
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.77,0:00:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.72,0:00:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.20,0:01:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(CHILDREN GROANING)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.33,0:01:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. All right.\NLet's get you in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.77,0:01:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gonna be okay,\Nkids. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got a heartbeat.\NJack? Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.68,0:01:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to step back.\NHe's my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.58,0:01:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack, wake up!\NCall your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.45,0:01:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them to go to\NPrinceton-Plainsboro Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our parents died.\NHe's all we've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was not parked illegally.\NI live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.60,0:02:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love note.\NFrom Detective Tritter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.00,0:02:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: Heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.44,0:02:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His cath was clean and\Necho showed no\Nstructural abnormalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.61,0:02:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fatigue, night sweats,\Nweight loss preceded\Nthe heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.74,0:02:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eighteen-year-old kid's\Nsuddenly an orphan\Nand a single father of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Party of Five.{\i0}\NPowerful stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.22,0:02:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The O.C.{\i0} of its day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stress explains everything\Nexcept the itchy feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Athlete's foot covers that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.49,0:02:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiters work 12 hours\Na day in old sneakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.\NIgnore the symptoms.\NMakes our job easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not ignoring a symptom.\NI'm explaining a symptom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.80,0:02:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's been hanging\Nover a toilet despite\Nantiemetic therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.03,0:02:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Persistent vomiting\Ncould indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.54,0:02:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,increased intracranial\Npressure, tumor...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.47,0:02:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Heart problems.\NIt's gotta be the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank God\Nthere's a neurologist\Nin the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.31,0:03:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. It's the feet.\NIf only I were a podiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.45,0:03:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably caught an intestinal\Nvirus from one of those\Nferal kids running around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.98,0:03:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeated vomiting causes\Nan electrolyte imbalance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which leads to an arrhythmia,\Nwhich leads to\Nthe heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And itchy feet.\NNope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.03,0:03:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it? Nope?\NI've said too much already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.43,0:03:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a game, House.\NNo, it's not. But it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.97,0:03:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you writing?\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you know the diagnosis,\Nwhy don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.70,0:03:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you gonna\Nlearn to swim
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.34,0:03:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unless I take off your\Nfloaties and throw you\Ninto shark-infested waters?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't know what's wrong\Nafter a 30-second\Nperusal of his file.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.58,0:03:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, you can't.\NNow, what's a game\Nwithout rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No tag-backs. No biting.\NYou get one test each.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.59,0:03:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the clock runs\Nuntil lunch. If I'm right,\Nhe'll still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.63,0:03:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm wrong,\Nthis is a very cruel game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.30,0:03:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,STEINERMAN: You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I charge for the time\Nyou were supposed to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tritter towed my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's frozen my assets.\NHe's on a crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a person of interest\Nin a narcotics investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're linked to their suspect\Nand his activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Pablo Escobar's\Nevil henchman cruising into\NMiami in a Cigarette boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.91,0:04:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a physician\Nwho prescribed Vicodin\Nto a pain patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.12,0:04:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This police report you faxed\Nme says they found 600 pills\Nin his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.82,0:04:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You prescribe those?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.05,0:04:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in chronic pain.\NThis is obviously\Nan abuse of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.96,0:04:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a yes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patients build up\Na tolerance over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect motive for him\Nto forge those scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still don't have an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we, like,\Nrole-playing?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.57,0:04:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you suck at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is really unfortunate,\Nbecause you're pretending\Nto be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta get to court.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael told me\Nyou could help me\Nget my car back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, divorce lawyers\Nusually know the ins and outs\Nof drug enforcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.61,0:04:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want your car back?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna have to\Ngive the cops what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Usually people\Nfeel helpless\Nin these situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.49,0:04:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. House is\Nprobably going to jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.99,0:04:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep on lying for him,\Nyou'll go right along\Nwith him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:05:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House was on this page\Nwhen he got that annoying\N"I'm such a genius" look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's there?\NPatient history.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's 18.\NProbably drinks,\Nsmokes, does drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.73,0:05:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How close am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit drugs when\Nhis parents died.\NQuit smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House didn't\Nmock my viral idea.\NHe just said it was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means\Nhe didn't want to\Ngive reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means\NI must have been close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.35,0:05:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking bacterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing a blood culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.59,0:05:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am doing an MRI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.16,0:05:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was a tumor,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.19,0:05:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,intracranial pressure could\Ncause his brain to\Nherniate before lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same thing with\Nthe stress test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.33,0:05:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why I'm ditching it.\NWhat are you doing instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.23,0:05:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?\NYou're playing his game?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all playing his game.\NMight as well enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.80,0:05:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody else sick at work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.17,0:05:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a stomachache\Nbefore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't your fault, Will.\NKeep working.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.01,0:05:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother's in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Collier won't care\Nif I finish my homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.35,0:05:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother cares\Nif you finish your homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I be your\Nimaginary friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.17,0:06:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are the feet?\NStill itch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that important?\NI don't know. Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.95,0:06:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kinds of drugs\Nyou into?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.11,0:06:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to\Ntalk about that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.75,0:06:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.85,0:06:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't keep secrets\Nfrom them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They know I did drugs\Nbefore our parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clever. Admit the past.\NDeny the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm raising two kids.\NIt'd be pretty irresponsible,\Nwouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.26,0:06:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But confiding in\Nan eight-year-old is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.73,0:06:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm open with them,\Nthen they'll be open with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\NTurning the other cheek's\Na good strategy in boxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids don't lie because\Nthey got trust issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They lie because\Nthey've got something to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.94,0:06:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's sitting there\Ndoing nothing\Nand he's still lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.48,0:06:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't lie to Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:06:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spelling test you failed\Nand forgot to...\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.75,0:07:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Math test?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.85,0:07:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight with the kid\Nsitting next to you?\NHe doesn't sit next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.75,0:07:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the other one's\Nprobably having sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.52,0:07:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not.\NYet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.39,0:07:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you start,\Nyou're gonna lie about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Colder.\NI'm not playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep very still for me, Jack.\NThis won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.98,0:07:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much dope did you smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.81,0:07:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he have to be here?\NNo. Ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not his lungs.\NI never said it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the cigarettes?\NHow'd you quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gum? The patch? Hypnosis?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went from two packs\Nto nothing, cold turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or we could just\Nmake small talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still seeing\Nthat nurse in Pedes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.90,0:07:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't think\Nshe's right for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.47,0:07:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need someone detached,\Ncalculating, ambitious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.57,0:07:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need yourself in a skirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.57,0:08:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack, he asked you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really quit.\NI just sort of\Nlost taste for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting. Sounds like\None of those symptom thingies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still puking,\Nand he had a heart attack\Nand itchy feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.79,0:08:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not his lungs.\NI never said it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ice cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.53,0:08:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm injecting ergonovine\Nto see if your heart attack
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.14,0:08:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was caused by\Na spasm in the vessels\Nsurrounding your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.91,0:08:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if\Nanything feels... unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.31,0:08:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the problems are at\Nmy heart, why did that other\Ndoctor look at my brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.78,0:08:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Why did\Nthat other doctor\Nlook at his brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.05,0:08:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just trying to eliminate\Nas many possibilities\Nas we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.49,0:08:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So because you think\Nthat a spasm caused\Nhis heart attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.56,0:08:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're gonna induce\Nanother spasm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.93,0:08:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you consent to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.03,0:08:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CAMERON:\NEverything's under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.37,0:09:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tests are gonna identify\Nwhich arteries are affected\Nso we can repair them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your meds don't seem\Nto be doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.17,0:09:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So either you're wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.94,0:09:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or his system hasn't\Nbeen pushed enough\Nto set anything off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.85,0:09:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna get back home,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're probably\Nalready falling behind with\Nthe housework and the bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many sick days\Nyou think you'll get\Nbefore they replace you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart rate's up. Nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.43,0:09:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't fire me\Nif I'm sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. You're irreplaceable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who else would they find\Nqualified to dance\Nwith a rodent?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you even\Nsupport your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.87,0:09:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happens when those kids\Ngrow out of their clothes?\NWhen they get sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still no spasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.45,0:09:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll take those kids\Naway from you, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.25,0:09:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should bring them\Nin here right now so that\Nyou can kiss them goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.85,0:09:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see\Nhis heart is fine!\NStop torturing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.66,0:09:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of doctor are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CUDDY: Wonderful.\NThank you so much. Okay, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just getting here?\NBusses suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your car?\NIt's a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.30,0:10:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tritter wants me to\Ntestify against House.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.61,0:10:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.94,0:10:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a question\Nor an order?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.84,0:10:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any sort of conviction\Nwill cost House\Nhis license...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.71,0:10:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which will cost\Nthis hospital. Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.25,0:10:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna mess\Nwith your precious resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.21,0:10:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told my lawyer to\Ntell Tritter to go to hell.\NMarco!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.55,0:10:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are all my prescriptions\Ngetting bounced back?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.52,0:10:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Dr. Wilson.\NI was trying to call you.\NWhere's your phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.29,0:10:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My patients,\Non the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are here and\Nneeded their medications.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.10,0:10:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I can't.\NYour DEA number's\Nbeen suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}HOUSE.: Why so sad?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.24,0:10:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a chance\Nthat Chase got it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(GROANS)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.97,0:10:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was suspenseful\Nfor about two seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood culture was\Nnegative for bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.35,0:10:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But positive for hepatitis A?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.48,0:10:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who could've ordered\Nthat extra test.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must be somebody who knew\Nwhat persistent vomiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.06,0:11:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sudden distaste for nicotine\Nand itchy feet have in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hep A doesn't explain\Nthe heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.03,0:11:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. But as Chase so deftly\Npointed out earlier,\Npuking does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And hep A\Nexplains the puking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this had been real life\Ninstead of just a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The DEA just revoked\Nmy prescription privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.88,0:11:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, who's gonna\Nprescribe my Vicodin?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well,\Nthat's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a disaster for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.71,0:11:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.38,0:11:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tritter's just getting\Ndesperate. He's got\Nno real evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.55,0:11:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to\Nsqueeze you into ratting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna\Nlet him squeeze my patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.52,0:11:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be fine.\NMost of your cancer medicine\Nsucks anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna use your team\Nto do my prescribing until\Nthis is straightened out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.86,0:11:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly this doesn't seem\Nnearly as dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go pump IVIG into the kid,\Ncure him and\Nget him out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.87,0:11:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hep A?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.41,0:11:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chase, blood test\Nfor bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Foreman, MRI,\Ntoo stubborn to\Ncheck the lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.55,0:12:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Cameron, nice try. No spasm."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"But the princess sat\Nand sat and sat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.06,0:12:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"pretending not to listen."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.49,0:12:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretending to write\Nin her journal\Nwith the flowers on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretending she didn't like\Nstories about eight-year-olds\Nwho save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.10,0:12:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why\Nyou can no longer\Nsave the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm eight!\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.54,0:12:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all completely\Ndependent on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.28,0:12:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.\NMorning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.65,0:12:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good news.\NWe can take you off the IVIG.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hep A has cleared\Nyour system. You'll be good\Nto go by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think I got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it could've been\Ncontaminated food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could've been from cleaning\Nthe bathrooms at work.\NOr it could've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.\NThey've heard it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.03,0:12:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anilingus is a common way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.23,0:12:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should just\Ntell the people\Nthat you've dated
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.04,0:12:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they should get\Nthemselves checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.57,0:12:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.71,0:13:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been too busy\Nchasing after these guys\Nto go spelunking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.51,0:13:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think.\NDoes your arm hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.45,0:13:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arm's fine, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.62,0:13:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why's it bleeding?\NIt's not. It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Raise your arm\Nabove your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ear... And your nose...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.74,0:13:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: High PT and PTT\Non Jack's blood panel\Nconfirm a coagulopathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.27,0:13:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we cure the hep A,\Nsomething else pops up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.85,0:13:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What infections cause DIC?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.99,0:13:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurt my shoulder\Nplaying fantasy football.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:13:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we discuss\Nwhat causes DIC,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.29,0:13:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or should we just\Nsend the kid back\Nto his miserable life?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.99,0:13:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not miserable.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's thrilled that\Nhis parents are dead\Nand his life is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The restaurant's probably\Nteeming with E. Coli,\NEikenella and strep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.80,0:14:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids don't wash their hands\Nbetween the potty\Nand the party and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or it's a food-borne toxin.\NJack eats at that cesspool\Nevery day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Jack's the only one\Nwho got sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's got tattoos, piercings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and probably\Nsome nasty little girl\Nwho loaned him the hep A.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.31,0:14:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could've also given him\Nsyphilis or gonorrhea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.48,0:14:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need one of you.\NTake Cameron.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.32,0:14:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your idea was dumb anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.55,0:14:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase, I need you to head back\Nto that cesspool and\Nget me the kid's puke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Foreman, do an LP\Nand have Cameron run down\Nthat potty-party theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.73,0:14:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't I just test him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not discuss this\Nin front of the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.47,0:14:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The amount of vomiting\Nthat kid did,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there wouldn't be enough\Ntoxins left in his system\Nto show up in his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.55,0:14:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since he vomited\Nin the toilet here\Ninstead of on somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.11,0:14:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that restaurant\Nis our only source\Nof essential vomit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.12,0:14:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you couldn't say that\Nin front of Foreman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.82,0:14:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I couldn't say this\Nin front of Foreman.\NI need a refill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:14:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Tritter knows about\Nthe scripts I wrote before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. If you stop now,\Nit'll look suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.53,0:15:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone fall\Nfor that argument?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Write the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.77,0:15:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One prescription\Nisn't gonna make...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We both know\Nit's not gonna be just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather lose my job\Nthan lose my license.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daniel Silvers, prostate\Ncancer. Needs filgrastim,\Ntwo-week supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Andrea Donovan,\Nbreast cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just needs her refill\Non her megestrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not writing.\NYou want me to write?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.46,0:15:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you could phone them in.\NBut eventually, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,probably somebody's gonna want\Nsomething written down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.40,0:15:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't met these people.\NI have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.31,0:15:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've diagnosed them\Nand everything.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.71,0:15:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I'm not saying\NI don't trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.21,0:15:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just my diagnoses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.71,0:15:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are gonna be\Nmy prescriptions. I...\NThey're my patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.42,0:15:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My prescriptions.\NMy name!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.19,0:16:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Tritter will read\Non the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.32,0:16:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to make you\Nmiserable. You don't think\Nhe's gonna ask questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.06,0:16:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.26,0:16:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything Jack does\Nthat no one else does?\NAny special duties?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.97,0:16:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we got lots of bussers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.40,0:16:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of cleaning products\Ndo you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got a bunch of kids\Nrunning around, sticking\Neverything in their mouths,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.61,0:16:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we can't use\Nanything toxic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.75,0:16:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it. Monday's trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no one\Nwho can maybe help\Nget the bags out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.42,0:16:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Short-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.46,0:16:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.19,0:16:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure Jack's puke\Nis in a blue trash bag\Nwith the wrapped gifts,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.36,0:16:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you find spaghetti\Nthat's the wrong vomit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much longer\Ndo I have to stay on\Nthis medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.01,0:17:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I'm nauseous\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.61,0:17:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should go back\Non the tamoxifen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.18,0:17:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing so much better\Non the anastrozole, Beth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm reluctant to\Nmake a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.02,0:17:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't play with my daughter\Nor pick her up from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can barely get up\Nand tuck her in at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.79,0:17:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's got to be\Nsomething else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.46,0:17:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.83,0:17:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as you know,\Nthis is a teaching hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.77,0:17:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a student?\NNo, I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.10,0:17:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm assisting\NDr. Wilson today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.84,0:17:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Do you think he got\Nmy diagnosis wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm sure...\NNo. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just consulting\Nregarding my prescriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think he got\Nmy meds wrong?\NNo. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.21,0:17:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.\NThen why is she here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.52,0:17:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.73,0:17:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna get a sample\Nof your brother's\Nspinal fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.03,0:17:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Will?\NSchool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.27,0:17:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that gonna hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gonna help us figure out\Nwhat's making him sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.67,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be\Nin class, too?\NTeacher work day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.37,0:18:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you but not Will?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.91,0:18:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, didn't make\Nsense to me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.61,0:18:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.32,0:18:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess it's quicker\Nthan calling a nurse\Nand a truant officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, grab his shins\Nand push his knees up\Ntowards his chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now hold him there tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This all nurses do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.57,0:18:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My boss doesn't trust them\Nto do anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(JACK GROANING)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.91,0:18:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he gonna die?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.95,0:18:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No one's gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.68,0:18:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the whole world ever?\NThat's so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I meant...\NI know what you meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I also know\Nbad things do happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.79,0:18:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad always had a few drinks\Nwhen they went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Always said\Nhe'd be okay to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until he wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.44,0:19:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would just like\Nsome warning this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're nowhere near\Nanything like that\Nhappening right now. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get him back over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(JACK SCREAMS)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.96,0:19:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.76,0:19:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You broke his rib?\NI barely touched him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(GROANS)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.40,0:19:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.\NFix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.60,0:19:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osteomyelitis.\NMeans the infection's\Nspread to his bones,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.04,0:19:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which means\Nit's either bacterial\Nor viral and not...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.31,0:19:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(GROANS)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.01,0:19:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hired you to\Ntake away the pain.\NWas there some confusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever thought about\Nusing your cane\Non the proper side?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.39,0:19:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.82,0:19:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Friday night my cane\Nsuddenly noticed\Nit was on the wrong side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.36,0:19:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you score me some Vicodin?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.83,0:20:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did a needle aspiration\Nto confirm which...\NHow long till the culture's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SCREAMS)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.93,0:20:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you only do that\Nwhen I'm talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.23,0:20:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta rest your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're gonna get you\Non some different equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice cane.\NIf I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.49,0:20:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase, you can stop\Ndoing that.\NI'm almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.49,0:20:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got osteomyelitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Means you're wrong\Nabout food-borne toxins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.90,0:20:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you can stop, too.\NIt's syphilis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.14,0:20:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure?\NRead the print out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.01,0:20:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also positive\Nfor Eikenella.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.45,0:20:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of you two screwed up.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.22,0:20:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.65,0:21:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or this kid is a lot sicker\Nthan we thought.\NFinish that test.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.06,0:21:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should be impossible\Nto get two right answers\Nto one question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.46,0:21:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay to have three?\NApparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.27,0:21:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CHASE: He's positive\Nfor botulism, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.10,0:21:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we knock down\None infection and\Nthree more pop up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.31,0:21:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this game is rigged.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.69,0:21:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.86,0:21:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody help!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.96,0:21:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: We've managed to\Nclear all three infections\Nout of his system,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.53,0:21:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now he's having seizures\Nevery few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.46,0:21:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gotta be\Nimmunocompromised.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.00,0:21:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,White count was normal,\Nand he was negative for HIV.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.40,0:21:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if he's not\Nimmunocompromised,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.67,0:21:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why is he acting like\Nhe's immunocompromised?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.50,0:21:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOUSE: What do\Nthe seizures tell us?\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.37,0:21:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no structural\Nabnormalities on the CT,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.51,0:21:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nonfocal neuro exam,\Nno electrolyte imbalance.\NNothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.61,0:22:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do unexplained seizures\Nand really sick 18-year-olds\Nhave in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.95,0:22:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You thinking trauma?\NI'm thinking drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.75,0:22:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an admitted user.\NThe drugs trashed\Nhis immune system.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tox screen was clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.29,0:22:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clean tox screen means\Nthere's no drugs\Nin his blood or urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.66,0:22:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There could still be drugs\Ntrapped in his fat cells\Nfrom the good old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.83,0:22:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're in his fat,\Nwhy would they be\Naffecting him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.47,0:22:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The keen observer would notice\Nthat he's had some\Ndigestive issues lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.37,0:22:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His weight loss\Ncould've burned off fat cells
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.74,0:22:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and released the drugs\Nback into his system.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.44,0:22:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: There's no way\Nto know. It's impossible to\Ntest fat cells for drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.68,0:22:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not impossible\Nto make him lose more weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.22,0:22:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to starve him\Nso we can drive him\Ninto another seizure?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.65,0:22:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a heart attack?\NJust so we can run\Nanother tox screen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.49,0:22:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be cruel.\NJust sweat it out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.73,0:22:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't touched a thing\Nsince the night\Nmy parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.47,0:22:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drugs stay in your system\Na long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was high the night\Nthe cops came to\Ntell us what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the first thing I did\Nwhen they told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.36,0:23:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.26,0:23:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the person\NI was when they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.80,0:23:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish they could see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.17,0:23:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure\Nthey're watching,\Nand I'm sure they're proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.24,0:23:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Will's\Nguidance counselor\Nkeeps telling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.84,0:23:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.24,0:23:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tell him it's crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our parents live on\Nin our memories,\Nbut they don't live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.79,0:23:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CHASE: Jack?\NCAMERON: Hold him still.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.26,0:23:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't break his arm.\NCAMERON: We'll fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.06,0:23:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get a sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.84,0:24:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.94,0:24:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.14,0:24:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't have sent\NCameron down here to\Nthis air-conditioned hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to deliver the bad news?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack seized again,\Nbut his blood was clean.\NCompletely drug free.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.58,0:24:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he just happened to have\Na seizure at the exact time\Nthat we stuck him in a sauna?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.88,0:24:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.09,0:24:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still seizing every\Nfew hours whether we stick\Nhim in a sauna or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.99,0:24:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God!\NWhy are you using that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.79,0:24:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had it for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.76,0:24:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's...\NThat's gonna make\Nyour shoulder hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.70,0:24:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.34,0:24:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.14,0:24:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he still infection-free?\NI'm sure not for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.07,0:24:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My point being that something\Nother than those infections\Ncaused these seizures.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.78,0:24:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Means there's something\Nin his head. Scan him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.41,0:24:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We scanned him.\NWell, that was then.\NThis is not then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.35,0:24:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid keeps changing.\NScan him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.65,0:24:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Cameron?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:24:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not writing you\Na script for Vicodin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.42,0:24:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only got two pills left.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.09,0:24:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut them in half.\NThen you'll have four.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.36,0:25:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're prescribing for Wilson.\NWilson prescribes for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.10,0:25:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Write up a script.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.53,0:25:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know\Nyou have a problem.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.57,0:25:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got a badge\Nand everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.93,0:25:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking too much...\NFine! You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.74,0:25:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the correct amount?\NWrite up a script\Nfor the correct amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.31,0:25:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No answer? That's 'cause\Nwe're having the wrong debate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.25,0:25:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This has got nothing\Nto do with my problem
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.78,0:25:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and everything to do with you\Navoiding a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.48,0:25:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're afraid that\Nif you write me a prescription
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.28,0:25:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're gonna wind up\Nlike Wilson.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.48,0:25:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.82,0:25:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tritter wants to win\Nby giving pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.36,0:25:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want\Nto be a part of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.59,0:25:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a doctor,\Nhow do you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.04,0:25:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.47,0:25:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll tide you over.\NTakes the edge off my PMS.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.44,0:25:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should do wonders for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.88,0:25:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you\Nlooking at my head again?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.42,0:26:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seizures usually indicate\Nsomething neurological.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.32,0:26:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.12,0:26:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.73,0:26:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll know more\Nafter the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.40,0:26:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta find out\Nwho can take care of\NWill and Kama.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.97,0:26:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not get ahead\Nof ourselves, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.10,0:26:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be home yelling at them\Nand kicking their butts\Nbefore you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.45,0:26:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(FOREMAN SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.62,0:26:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This kid might be facing\Na terminal disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.68,0:26:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's more worried\Nabout his brother and sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.75,0:26:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CHASE: Brain stem's clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.92,0:26:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in the midbrain.\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.02,0:26:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The frontal lobe,\Nupper-right quadrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.79,0:26:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything.\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.46,0:26:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's tiny,\Nbut I think it's a tumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.87,0:26:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That size should be excisable.\NWhy didn't we see it earlier?\NHow could...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.64,0:26:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.21,0:26:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Axial view.\NThere's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.18,0:26:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring up the next slice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.15,0:27:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.55,0:27:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack's brain is\Nriddled with tumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.89,0:27:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you know what he's doing?\NMoaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.59,0:27:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Setting up play dates.\NWow, what a guy. Theories?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.03,0:27:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The obvious one,\Nbrain cancer destroyed\Nhis immune system,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.40,0:27:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,left him wide open\Nfor these infections.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.30,0:27:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House, you're pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.94,0:27:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll analyze\Nanyone's faults,\Nhypocrisies, weaknesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.34,0:27:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this kid's\Ngot some strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.61,0:27:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all of a sudden\Nthere's no time to talk about\Nanything but the medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.68,0:27:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's teaching pre-pubescent\Nkids that truth matters,\NGod doesn't and life sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.85,0:27:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like him. Treatment?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.62,0:27:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to\Nstart him on radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.58,0:27:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll destroy\Nwhatever's left of\Nhis immune system.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.75,0:27:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: And save his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.86,0:27:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the notion\Nof self-sacrifice\Nis foreign to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.39,0:27:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna think that he's\Nsacrificing himself because\Nif one person can do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then maybe the world\Nisn't the cold, selfish place\Nyou know that it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.57,0:27:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Radiation could kill him.\NAlternatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.77,0:27:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any.\NWe saw the tumors...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.27,0:28:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could choose\Nto say they aren't tumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.81,0:28:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're just pus, which\Nwould explain why they\Nweren't there yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.08,0:28:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be an infection.\NHe got IVIG,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.81,0:28:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,broad-spectrum antibiotics...\NExactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.58,0:28:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Creates a perfect world\Nfor fungus, moves in,\Ngets married,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.29,0:28:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has little fungi...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.39,0:28:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're wrong about\Nthe fungus, you're wasting\Nwhat little time he has left.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.06,0:28:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a big sacrifice.\NHis life sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.06,0:28:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's be right.\NGo stick a needle\Nin the kid's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.90,0:28:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you suck out a liquid,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.03,0:28:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then I'm right\Nand we haven't\Nanswered anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.60,0:28:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you suck out a solid,\Nyou're right and no more\Nworrying about play dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.34,0:28:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Fine.\NI'll father your child.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.51,0:28:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you got to write me\Na Vicodin prescription,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.15,0:28:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just so I can\Nget through the foreplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.85,0:28:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many days\Ndo you have left?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.18,0:28:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could probably get through\Nmaybe the next minute or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.95,0:28:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your coming to me means\Nyour lackeys actually\Nstood up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.52,0:28:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.69,0:28:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, their cowardice\Nis inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.83,0:28:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you should be\Nthanking them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.80,0:28:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they caved,\Nit'd give the cops evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.90,0:29:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you intimidated\Nunderlings to\Nfeed your addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.13,0:29:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate writing\Nthank-you notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.94,0:29:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be weird if I asked\NCameron to write them?\NYou're hooking me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.87,0:29:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately,\Nif I cut you off,\Nit'd give the cops evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.94,0:29:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you don't really\Nneed the pain meds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.38,0:29:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that cleavage\Nwas a smokescreen.\NYou're a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.98,0:29:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't lift your arm.\NYou can't pee standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.52,0:29:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme.\NYou been doing physio?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.42,0:29:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you pulled...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.52,0:29:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Been training for\N{\i1}Pants-Off Dance-Off.{\i0}\NGive me the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.03,0:29:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your shoulder problem\Nisn't physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.60,0:29:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll find out\Nif you ever give me that...\NWhat's new?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.73,0:29:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's different?\NAny big changes\Nin your life recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.03,0:29:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight with the wife maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.47,0:29:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good.\NMeans your shoulder's\Na human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.21,0:29:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a start.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.64,0:29:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right. Right?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.05,0:29:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just not about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.59,0:30:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.76,0:30:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were abscesses\Nfrom a fungal infection.\NAspergillus.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.53,0:30:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: But we still have\Nno idea why.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.57,0:30:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our kid's immune system\Nhas a factory defect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.54,0:30:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOUSE: It's genetic.\NIt can't be genetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.54,0:30:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've been\Ngetting infections\Nsince he was an infant.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.67,0:30:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not if he grew up in a bubble.\NOr if he grew up on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.04,0:30:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No germs there, either.\NI don't mean a literal bubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.05,0:30:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sweet suburban bubble\Nwhere mommies and daddies\Nprotect their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.58,0:30:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They die. Bubble bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.69,0:30:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuing emotional trauma\Ntriggers the genetic illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.32,0:30:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Question is, which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.89,0:30:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOUSE: The infections\Nhe's contracted\Nnarrow down the possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.73,0:30:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hep A indicates\Na problem with his B cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.90,0:30:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bruton's Agammaglobulinemia?\NEikenella.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.40,0:30:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Points to\Na complement deficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.90,0:30:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(DOOR OPENS)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.04,0:30:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a patient. I need...\NNot now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.04,0:30:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go.\NYou'll stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.97,0:30:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patient's dying.\NSo is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.21,0:30:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in the next hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.38,0:30:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does\Nthe syphilis tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.32,0:30:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.85,0:31:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could mean\Nchronic granulomatous disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.35,0:31:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the aspergillus is\Na T cell issue. Common\Nvariable immunodeficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.13,0:31:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genetic testing's\Ngonna take time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.30,0:31:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given the rate\Nhe's picking up infections...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.86,0:31:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we\Nturn it into a race?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.30,0:31:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little late to be\Nplaying games with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.90,0:31:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not you guys. The infections.\NWhat infections?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.00,0:31:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The infections\Nwe're gonna give him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.31,0:31:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to cure me\Nis to make me sicker?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.14,0:31:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of the four\Npossible genetic conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.41,0:31:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is most susceptible to\Ndifferent types of infection.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.85,0:31:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.89,0:31:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a cocktail of\Nserratia, meningococcus,\Ncepacia and rhinovirus.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.16,0:31:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whichever germ\Ngains the most ground
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.63,0:31:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,plants the flag\Nof its leader,\Ngives us our answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.73,0:31:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how are you\Ngonna know which one\Ngains the most ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.97,0:31:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's the fun part.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.94,0:31:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, if the meningococcus\Nis king of the hill, you get\Nto have another seizure.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.27,0:31:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Serratia will shut down\Nyour lungs. If it's cepacia,\Nyou'll have a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.34,0:32:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it's the rhinovirus,\Nyou'll sneeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.75,0:32:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't all be dramatic.\NWe good?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.28,0:32:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.52,0:32:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the alternative is\Nwe guess, and there's\Na three out of four chance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.72,0:32:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that your little brother\Nand sister will get to\Ncry over another coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.06,0:32:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You study fractions in school?\NWe good?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.40,0:32:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.01,0:32:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(COUGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.38,0:32:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this test isn't\Nexactly FDA approved,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.61,0:32:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so let's just keep it\Nour little secret, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.41,0:33:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(COUGHING)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.96,0:33:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(GASPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.34,0:33:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(GASPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.54,0:33:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(THUNDER RUMBLING)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.38,0:33:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(CUDDY CLEARS THROAT)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.55,0:33:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little Orphan Annie and\NOliver Twist slept in\Nour hallways last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.48,0:33:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they singing?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.75,0:33:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're children.\NThey need a guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.72,0:33:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't find a babysitter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.06,0:33:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on account of not being able\Nto make any phone calls,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.19,0:33:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on account of\Nnot being able to breathe,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.53,0:33:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on account of his lungs\Nfilling up with serratia.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.16,0:33:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has chronic\Ngranulomatous disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.87,0:34:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Game over.\NOur work is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.57,0:34:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he's gonna\Nkeep getting sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.54,0:34:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta call\NSocial Services.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.37,0:34:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bone marrow transplant\Nwould re-boot\Nhis whole immune system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.34,0:34:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be healthy enough to win\NMiserable Daddy of the Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.08,0:34:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So see if one of\Nhis kids is a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.88,0:34:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My kids are\Nalready testing his kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.35,0:34:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FOREMAN: Will's a match.\NYou tested him?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.85,0:34:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never consented for that.\NIt's just a blood draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.89,0:34:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no danger.\NTo the testing.\NWhat about the surgery?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.36,0:34:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The risk for Will\Nis next to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.26,0:34:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(MACHINE BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.23,0:34:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if I don't do it?\NWhat are my other options?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.87,0:34:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your immune system\Ncan't fight off the germs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.24,0:34:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we all come into contact\Nwith every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.54,0:34:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we know,\Nwe can use more\Ntargeted medications,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.78,0:34:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you'll still get sick\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.15,0:34:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be in and out\Nof hospitals...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.88,0:34:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll live.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.26,0:34:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.56,0:35:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your lifespan will be\Nsubstantially shortened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.63,0:35:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll be too sick\Nto care for your brother\Nand sister anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.37,0:35:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have\Npressured him into...\NThere was no pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.67,0:35:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's eight years old!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.74,0:35:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tell him\Nhis brother's dying\Nunless he helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.67,0:35:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think\Nhe's gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.78,0:35:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to help you.\NHe has no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.05,0:35:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you asked him to\Nlet me play with one of his\Ntoys. This is surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.82,0:35:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could die.\NHe'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.15,0:35:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.92,0:35:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna have a hard time\Nprotecting him like this\Nif you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.30,0:35:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.03,0:35:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when Will's 18\Nand can decide for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.64,0:35:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(THUNDER RUMBLING)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.84,0:35:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noble.\NMoronic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.58,0:35:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a synonym.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.12,0:36:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you accept\Nhe wants to\Nprotect his brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.99,0:36:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has to protect his brother.\NDoesn't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.59,0:36:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wants to run screaming\Nfrom protecting his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.59,0:36:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a hypocrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.66,0:36:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Evidence is everything.\NTruth is all that matters."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.94,0:36:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except when\Nit comes to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.47,0:36:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything we've learned\Nabout this kid says\Nyou're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.24,0:36:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.08,0:36:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to\Nreject the diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.61,0:36:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so easy to\Nreject your misanthropy,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.05,0:36:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because then\Nyou'd have to give people\Na fighting chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.65,0:36:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that scares\Nthe crap out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.79,0:36:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.30,0:36:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get some evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.81,0:36:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your lucky day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.37,0:36:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOUSE: Just found another\Ndonor in the registry.\NPerfect match.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.91,0:37:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can do the transplant\Nwith no danger to the rug rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.71,0:37:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just have to sign here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.88,0:37:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless there's another reason\Nyou don't want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.32,0:37:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a chance I'd die.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.06,0:37:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A chance you'll be cured.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.93,0:37:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you don't\Nwant that, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.46,0:37:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe hanging out in\Na hospital getting waited on\Nhand and foot
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.40,0:37:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,reminds you of what life used\Nto be like before you were\Nforced to play Mister Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.70,0:37:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like being sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.60,0:37:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't want\Nto be healthy, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.74,0:37:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.48,0:37:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilt free.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.08,0:37:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'd do it\Nwhen Will's 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.31,0:37:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's able to take care\Nof himself without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.72,0:37:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack, your brother\Nand sister need you.\NI know!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.42,0:37:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know every second of\Nevery day that they need me,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.89,0:37:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm too young\Nto be their dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.27,0:37:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.01,0:38:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pretend\Nyou're surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.53,0:38:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to go throw stuff\Nat people off the balcony?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.17,0:38:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Mail can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.63,0:38:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm referring my patients\Nto other oncologists.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.04,0:38:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm shutting down my practice.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.91,0:38:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I was afraid\Nyou might overreact.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.34,0:38:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just ask\Nmy patients to wait
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.08,0:38:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because Dr. Cameron's boss\Nwon't let her come out\Nand play!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.81,0:38:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept you waiting\Nfor maybe an hour...\NThree hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.45,0:38:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody die?\NNot this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.98,0:38:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cameron's available now.\NUse her all you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.12,0:38:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So now's a better time for me\Nto have my life taken away?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.72,0:38:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It fits into\Nyour schedule better?\NOh, poor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.93,0:38:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think if you suffer\Nloudly enough...\NYou committed a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.96,0:38:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want me to do?\NTurn myself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.53,0:39:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Yes! Do something!\NGo in! Show some remorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.10,0:39:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Tritter\Nyou'll get some help!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.57,0:39:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need help!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.81,0:39:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House, get out of here.\NGet out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.55,0:39:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are not gonna make me\Nfeel guilty about what\NTritter is doing to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.62,0:39:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SCOFFS)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.22,0:39:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.89,0:39:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mysterious shoulder pain\Nisn't coming from your cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.59,0:39:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from\Nyour conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.63,0:39:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That used to be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.90,0:39:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all\Nyour smartass remarks,\NI knew you gave a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.63,0:39:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.44,0:39:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were either gonna\Nhelp me through this\Nor you weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.01,0:39:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got my answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.46,0:39:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's gonna\Ndrive me to school,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.36,0:40:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,help me with my homework?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.76,0:40:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There'll be a mom\Nwhere they take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.63,0:40:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A real mom,\Nsomeone who can cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.47,0:40:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.\NI'll still be able to\Nsee you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.55,0:41:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said\Nyou'd make him better.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.86,0:41:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.84,0:41:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you\Nfor not telling them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.67,0:41:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a good kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.94,0:41:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three months from now,\Nsix months from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.85,0:41:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be visiting them\Nand you won't be able\Nto say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.35,0:41:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna know\Nyou screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.79,0:41:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll take his bone marrow\Nand you'll take them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.00,0:41:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they'll be a burden\Nand a pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.43,0:41:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and your life will never be\Nwhat it was supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.04,0:41:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you'll be proud\Nof yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.71,0:42:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your parents,\Nthey'll be proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.85,0:42:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.46,0:42:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.06,0:42:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's what I wanna believe.